<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DCM AND DDM DRUM TYPE PARKING BRAKE - ROCKWELL DUPLEX CAM MECHANICAL BRAKE - LUBRICATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="lubricate" graphiccount="0">
        <title>LUBRICATION</title>
        <para>Before assembly, apply a thin layer of NLGI Grade No. 2 lithium grease to the following parts:</para>
        <seqlist style="arabic">
            <item>
                <para>Cam head, face and journals.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>The point that the shoe webs and the actuator strut make contact.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Both sides of the backing plate at the cam hole.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Backing plate shoe-guide lugs and shoe bearing surfaces.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Backing plate anchor pins.</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Do not permit grease to come in contact with the brake drum or linings. Grease on the linings will
                    cause poor brake performance.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
